  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Dear sir</p>
         <p>I feel great pleasure in having this opportunity of introducing to you my respected friend <persName ref="prsn:Morr01">Mr. Thos. Morrison Sen[io]r</persName> of <placeName ref="tgn:7009554">Dunfermline</placeName> to whom you, the public &amp; myself are much indebted for the exertion he has made in obtaining for the "Dispatch" an extensive circulation in Dunfermline &amp; neighbourhood;</p>
         <p>He visits <placeName ref="tgn:7011781">London</placeName> with the intention of delivering a course of lectures on astronomy &amp; also on Politics. the former in opposition to the Newtonian System &amp; the latter in accordance with the principles of <persName ref="Cobb01">Cobbett</persName>: he has delivered the same course to crowded audiences [[2]] in <placeName ref="tgn:7009546">Edin.</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="tgn:7017283">Glasgow</placeName>, with great "eclat".</p>
         <p>I sincerely wish that he may find the same response in London.</p>
         <p>Whatever you may do in directing public attention to Mr. Morrison I shall consider as a favour done myself.</p>
         <p>I am | dear sir</p> 
         <p>yours &amp;c &amp;c</p>
         <p>Alexr McKerracher</p>
      </body>
